---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="About Ajaycent Angles and the person behind it."
	pubDate={new Date('July 17 2026')}
>
	<p>
		Ajaycent Angles is written by Ajay Phatak — essays on tech, finance, politics, and
		philosophy, and the places where they intersect. The name nods to <em>adjacent angles</em>:
		in geometry, two angles that share a common side. Most of what's written here lives on
		those shared edges.
	</p>

	<p>
		Alongside the essays, the site hosts live data projects, starting with the
		<a href="https://elections.ajaycent.com">2026 Election Tracker</a> — a dashboard following
		Senate and House races through the 2026 midterms, with polling trends, race ratings,
		betting odds, and news for every contest.
	</p>

	<p>
		Questions, corrections, or disagreements are welcome:
		<a href="mailto:ajay.phatak2@gmail.com">ajay.phatak2@gmail.com</a>.
	</p>
</Layout>
